custom_minimum_size = Vector2(100, 0)
layout_mode = 2
size_flags_vertical = 1
text = "In code you append entries with row_scene.instantiate() → entries_vbox.add_child(row). That gives you an unbounded, append-only list you can scroll through. If you later want load-more when reaching the bottom, connect to the scroll bar’s value_changed and append the next page of rows — still using the same ScrollContainer + VBoxContainer pattern.

What each control is good for:

Control	Scrolling	Many journal rows
VBoxContainer alone
No
Stacks children only
ScrollContainer + VBoxContainer + row scenes
Yes
Best default for multi-line entry previews
ItemList (used correctly, via add_item)
Yes (built-in)
Good for one-line titles; pair with a sibling TextEdit for full entry on select
VBoxContainer without ScrollContainer
No
Not suitable for a long journal history
"
autowrap_mode = 3

